s=\"fn\">{a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(b : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{as : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem\">List.Mem</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">as</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem\">List.Mem</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">::</a> <span class=\"fn\">as</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/128a1e6b0a82718382f9c39c79be44ff3284547c/src/Init/Data/List/Basic.lean#L736-L737","name":"List.Mem.head","line":736,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem.head","doc":"The head of a list is a member: `a ∈ a :: as`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem.head\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">Mem</span>.<span class=\"name\">head</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(as : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem\">List.Mem</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">::</a> <span class=\"fn\">as</span>)</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/128a1e6b0a82718382f9c39c79be44ff3284547c/src/Init/Data/List/Basic.lean#L730-L739","name":"List.Mem","line":730,"kind":"inductive","docLink":"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem","doc":"`a ∈ l` is a predicate which asserts that `a` is in the list `l`.\nUnlike `elem`, this uses `=` instead of `==` and is suited for mathematical reasoning.\n* `a ∈ [x, y, z] ↔ a = x ∨ a = y ∨ a = z`\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.Mem\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">Mem</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/128a1e6b0a82718382f9c39c79be44ff3284547c/src/Init/Data/List/Basic.lean#L726-L726","name":"List.contains_nil","line":726,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.contains_nil","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.contains_nil\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">contains_nil</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">[]</span>.contains</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/128a1e6b0a82718382f9c39c79be44ff3284547c/src/Init/Data/List/Basic.lean#L723-L724","name":"List.contains","line":723,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.contains","doc":"`O(|l|)`.\n`l.contains a` or `elem a l` is true if there is an element in `l` equal (according to `==`) to `a`.\n\n* `[1, 4, 2, 3, 3, 7].contains 3 = true`\n* `[1, 4, 2, 3, 3, 7].contains 5 = false`\n\nThe preferred simp normal form is `l.contains a`, and when `LawfulBEq α` is available,\n`l.contains a = true ↔ a ∈ l` and `l.contains a = false ↔ a ∉ l`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.contains\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">contains</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#BEq\">BEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span